				\begin{document}$${\mu }_{slurry}={\mu }_{carrier fluid}(1+k\phi )$$\end{document}where k takes the value 2.5 for rigid spherical particles based on rigidity and Brownian motion (Vand 1945). However, when ePCM particles move relative to each other under the shearing motion of fluid, they collide and roll over each other, the duration of which is directly proportional to the concentration of ePCM particles in the CF.

