Thomas (1965) made a comparison of the values given by the Vand formulation with experimental results and reported that the degree of agreement is 97.5%, which gradually decreases to 60% for a concentration of 40% and to an unacceptable degree of 8.7% when the concentration reaches 60%. As a result, a better-fit version of the formulation was proposed by Thomas (1965) in order to maintain high agreement rates even for greater concentrations:5μeff=μfl+2.5ϕ+10.05ϕ2+0.00273exp16.6ϕ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
