				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\dot{m}$$\end{document}=0:67 kg/s, proving the superiority of ePCM-S over water as a HTF. Nevertheless, both initial setup costs and operating costs of ePCM-S-based PVT are higher when compared to conventional PVT-liquid systems (Ali 2017).Fig. 25
